            "body": "Hi Heath,<br><br><br>Thanks for coming back to me with your advice. I really appreciate it.<br><br><br>I'm just trying to figure out my way around this quite technical content on the site and try to get our research team to be thinking more about SEO and keywords when they are writing content.<br><br><br>Basically I think everyone is keen to have a bullet summary somewhere so that if people don't want to/don't have time they can just read that instead of the full article. So would your suggestion be to have the format of the articles as follows?<br><br><br>\u00b7 Headline<br><br>\u00b7 Bullet point summary<br><br>\u00b7 First para + main article<br><br><br>Also, do you know if google counts the first bullet point as the first paragraph if it sits as the first item in the main body of the article?<br><br><br>Thanks<br><br><br>Lizzy",
            "source": {
